<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="16Mar1927"><font color="red">16 March 1927</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Harriet Weaver): The P.E.N. club of London invited James the Punman to be guest of honour at a dinner in London on 5 April &hellip; We leave here on 29 instant as it takes a week to cross the Woebegone &hellip; <i>Transition</i> is held up a week by legal formalities but I suppose, as you don&apos;t like <font face="wake">w</font> any better in his nice print frock that he will not appeal to you even in his 39 articles of clothing. As for me I am working away at the suite (I will sell my chance of going to London to end it all every word. O go on, go on, go on!). The typescript is like a caviare sandwich </div>
